</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,266,581]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,366,266,292]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Species richness:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose" authorityYear="1922" box="[366,450,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Frailea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[366,450,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Frailea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises 19 species according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Gerloff, N." box="[851,1018,266,292]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160" pagination="138 - 147" refId="ref8364" refString="Gerloff, N. (2001) Frailea densispina (Hofacker &amp; Herm) N. Gerloff, Comb. &amp; Stat. Nov. Cactus &amp; Co 3 (5): 138 - 147." type="journal article" year="2001">Gerloff (2001)</bibRefCitation>
. Twelve are endemic, recognized only for 
<collectingRegion box="[176,448,302,328]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Rio Grande do Sul State</collectingRegion>
(Pontes 
<emphasis box="[546,602,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">et al.</emphasis>
2018).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,266,581]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,471,338,364]" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">General distribution:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose" authorityYear="1922" box="[471,555,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Frailea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[471,555,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Frailea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a restricted geographical distribution to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1151,1222,338,364]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1233,1338,339,365]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1348,1447,339,365]" name="Uruguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
, southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[283,368,374,400]" name="Bolivia" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, and northeast 
<collectingCountry box="[535,650,374,400]" name="Argentina" pageId="7" pageNumber="160">Argentina</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
